1118579604363665409.text:
At @NASA_Wallops, it’s a beautiful day for a launch! At 4:46pm ET, @NorthropGrumman’s #Cygnus lifts off, sending 7,600 pounds of cargo to @Space_Station. 

Watch live at 4:15pm ET: https://go.nasa.gov/2UHQXc9 
Live in the U.S. mid-Atlantic? You might see it: https://go.nasa.gov/2UHVQlF pic.twitter.com/vcssDG7kVj

1116857427515908099.text:
С ДНЕМ КОСМОНАВТИКИ! 

58 years ago today; April 12, 1961; Yuri Gagarin became the first human in space.

Celebrating the historic 108-minute flight in his Vostok 1 spacecraft at #YurisNight in ‘Believeland’! 

Он Сказал Поехали! 
#ДеньКосмонавтики #Поехали #ЮрийГагаринpic.twitter.com/tMXSsBGyrU

1113812013040295936.text: Russia's Progress 72 cargo ship docked at 10:22am ET today to the station's Pirs docking compartment 254 miles over central China delivering 3.7 tons of supplies. #AskNASA | https://go.nasa.gov/2IaDAKd pic.twitter.com/bcEYFt3wsp

1118941289595199490.text: Taking @Space_Station’s robotic arm for a spin! Tomorrow, @AstroAnnimal will capture the Cygnus cargo vehicle using the CanadaArm2 as Cygnus holds position just 30ft from station. We all got a turn practicing on the real robotic arm for the first time to prep for the big arrival!pic.twitter.com/KMkSKztFa5

1121180212752994305.text: Runner’s high! Yesterday our treadmill finally called it quits after outlasting its expected lifetime by years. I replaced it with a new unit so we could get back to our exercise routine of strength training & cardio every day. Running helps counteract the impacts of microgravitypic.twitter.com/N4bpDFi0eC

1120773882460422144.text: Bring on the delicate tasks! I got to reconfigure the Advanced Combustion Microgravity Experiment, enabling scientists to keep pushing the envelope in fuel efficiency and pollutant reduction for combustion processes on Earth. Did you know flames burn like spheres in microgravity?pic.twitter.com/16cUdvlRmy

1122203007872114691.text: Clouds stole the view east of Adelaide to the @wsl at Bells, but I bet you could have seen the waves themselves from the @Space_Station!  Way to crush the ‘50 Year Storm,’ Courtney Conlogue (@neonboho)!  #swellfromspacepic.twitter.com/5Ha44GtfD8

1121770219284959232.text: One of the last frontiers I can’t wait to explore one day, Alaska’s unmistakable Aleutian Islands.pic.twitter.com/NWU3yaQTur

1113964742794674176.text: Glad to have another 3.7 tons of supplies and science joining us!

1119007167380631555.text: The solar arrays do their work during our daylight, but they seem to be most beautiful at sunset. Tomorrow a new pair of solar arrays will join the mix on the #CygnusNG11 cargo vehicle when it berths to @Space_Station!pic.twitter.com/WozLdnPlBJ

1113844968039354369.text: “Float right there.” Words I never thought I’d hear my eye doctor say. Starting a week of baseline medical data collection to compare with later in flight. Long duration microgravity studies so we can set our sights on deep space!pic.twitter.com/djUqS0kuQn

1116322771817172992.text: Gardening without gravity. Dedicating this space harvest to my grandfather, a farmer who taught me not only the value of hard work but to love what you do. He would've liked that we are doing research to benefit future space travel, & taking time at the end to celebrate together.pic.twitter.com/SPkLbNIYxN

1118201315337830403.text: Our vestibular systems behave differently when we are in microgravity. The VECTION experiment from @csa_asc is helping scientists better understand these changes, and develop ways to adapt. I tested https://go.nasa.gov/2DzGrd8 pic.twitter.com/4XHj8EeBMJ

1118491046038646784.text: One month down. Ten to go. Today the possibility has become reality: My mission is planned to be extended through a third Expedition onboard @Space_Station! Privileged to contribute my best every single day of it.pic.twitter.com/b9RhhNHZzt

1116043954707996674.text: Eyes on.  Duranbah Beach, Gold Coast, Australia--first stop of the World Surf League Championship Tour--from the @Space_Station. Congratulations, @caroline_markss on your first @wsl CT win!  #SwellFromSpacepic.twitter.com/SxYB9QeSkC

1120434255581130755.text: It took my breath away as it came into focus. My first glimpse of coastal North Carolina from space. It’s a special thing to see from above the place where you grew up--the ocean that first inspired my fascination with things that make me feel small & planted the seed to explore.pic.twitter.com/OZoqiOVtRR

1119213251643027456.text: Cygnus captured! Congratulations to the team and @AstroAnnimal for a job well done. Next step, mission control operates the arm to berth Cygnus to the docking port.pic.twitter.com/BWSIQyIBfl

1115612652477321218.text: Three weeks. Three spacewalks. It’s the things you do, and more importantly, the people you do them with.pic.twitter.com/MrsTxLHupF

1113964738281656322.text: So close, yet so far. As the Progress cargo spacecraft autonomously docked just 20 feet away, we were watching it on a TV stream beamed up from Earth! Gotta have the @Space_Station window shutters closed to protect them from the docking rocket engine plumes.pic.twitter.com/d97I79gArM
